FBNInsurance Limited has paid N9.92 billion claims to its policyholders who suffered insured risks in 2019. This translates to about 130 percentage growth when compared to N4.31 billion claims paid in its 2018 financial year end. Speaking on this development, its managing director/CEO, Mr Val Ojumah, said: “As a responsive and reliable insurer that keeps its promises, we promptly paid claims to our clients to the tune of N9.92 billion which is a 130 per cent increase from N4.31 billion paid in 2018. “Our strategy remains providing financial security for our esteemed customers and as always, we will not fail to exceed our customers’ and stakeholders’ expectations.” At FBNInsurance, he stressed, prompt settlement of customers’ claims is key to the success of its business, which is continually boosting customers’ confidence and trust in the company. An anonymous customers who spoke at the company’s 5th Customer Forum in Uyo, Akwa-Ibom State recently, said: “FBNInsurance is one insurer I am proud to be associated with because of their commitment in ensuring customer’s satisfaction and happiness. I can boldly say I have no regret buying insurance policies from them.” Earlier, FBNInsurance had won the 2019 Best Life Insurance Company in Nigeria Award at the World Finance Award held in London. FBNInsurance Limited is an FBNHoldings Company associated with the Sanlam Group of South Africa. 